content.value:
"trans kids didn't exist before"

Bitch look at me. Look at how happy I was, how fucking cute I was.

It still took me 13 more years to actually realize I could just be a girl if I wanted to. We've always been here, we just lacked the concepts, words and resources to come out.

photo.alt: Picture of me when I was 12, wearing a dark green skirt and a flowery blouse. My legs are crossed and i have shoulder length hair
